The President made remarks in the Cabinet Room about the urgent need to rebuild and restore America's infrastructure. He discussed a $1.5 trillion investment in American infrastructure, a faster permitting process, $50 billion for rural infrastructure and internet access, a workforce initiative, and giving more power to state and local governments to choose projects. The President emphasized the importance of focusing on rebuilding the country's own infrastructure after spending trillions of dollars overseas. He expressed optimism about finding common ground between Republicans and Democrats on this issue and praised the recently passed bill to support the military. The President concluded by stating that the discussion on infrastructure would now begin.